U.S. stocks pared losses as retailers
rallied and financial shares trimmed declines after JPMorgan
Chase & Co. said it has funds to buy back at least $1 billion in
shares.  JPMorgan rallied 1.5 percent to lead the  Dow Jones
Industrial Average  higher as Chief Executive Officer  Jamie Dimon 
said that the bank may or may not repurchase more shares.  The Standard & Poorâ€™s 500 Index was down less than 0.1
percent at 1,257.35 at 12:27 p.m. in New York after slumping as
much as 1.1 percent. The Dow climbed 28.42 points, or 0.2
